olive oil
2 potatoes
1 bunch baby broccoli
3 clove garlic
½ orange
2 tbs milk
1 packet Lamb Shortloin
1 packet Apricot Sauce
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
1 bag parsley
40 g butter (for the mash)
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 tbs water
20 g butter (for the sauce)
½ tbs vinegar (balsamic or white wine)

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water, then add a generous pinch of salt.
• Peel potato and cut into large chunks.
• Halve any thicker stalks of baby broccoli lengthways. Finely chop garlic. Zest orange (see ingredients) to get a pinch and cut orange into wedges.

TIP: Save time and get more fibre by leaving the potato unpeeled!

• Cook potato in boiling water, over high heat, until easily pierced with a fork, 12-15 minutes.
• Drain and return potato to the pan.
• Add butter (for the mash), the milk and shredded Cheddar cheese to the potato.
• Mash until smooth. Cover to keep warm.

• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook baby broccoli and a dash of water until tender, 5-6 minutes.
• Add half the garlic and cook until fragrant, 30 seconds. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to a bowl and cover to keep warm.

• Season lamb shortloin on both sides.
• Return the pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook lamb for 5-6 minutes, each side, or until cooked to your liking. Transfer to a plate to rest for 5 minutes and cover to keep warm.

• While the lamb is resting, combine apricot sauce, vegetable stock powder, orange zest, a squeeze of orange juice and a drizzle of vinegar in a small bowl.
• Return the frying pan to medium heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Add remaining garlic and cook until fragrant, 30 seconds.
• Add the orange juice mixture and the water and simmer until thickened, 1-2 minutes. Remove pan from heat, then stir through butter (for the sauce).

• Thinly slice lamb.
• Divide cheesy mash, baby broccoli and lamb between plates. Spoon over orange glaze.
• Tear over parsley leaves to serve. Enjoy!